Utterance: Hi Tatiana, welcome back! How was your trip to Hawaii?
Oh my gosh, it was amazing! Just what I needed. The beaches, the food, everything was just perfect.
That sounds wonderful! Did you find it relaxing?
Totally! I really got to disconnect from everything. I even tried surfing!
Wow, that’s impressive! How did that go?
It was challenging but fun! I fell a lot, but I think I got the hang of it by the end of the trip.
That’s great to hear! Trying new things can be so rewarding. Did you feel any different when you returned?
Yeah, I felt lighter, you know? Like I could breathe again. But now that I’m back, reality is hitting me hard.
What do you mean by reality?
Just the job search and feeling stuck again. It’s like, I was so free there, and now I’m back to stressing about money and work.
It’s understandable to feel that way. Do you have any strategies to cope with that stress?
I’ve been trying to keep up with my workouts and photography, but it’s hard when I feel overwhelmed.
That makes sense. How do you feel about incorporating more of those activities into your routine?
I think I need to make it a priority. It just gets hard to motivate myself when I feel down.
Perhaps we can set some small, achievable goals for you to help with that?
Yeah, I’d like that.
Great! How about setting a goal to take a photo every day or go for a short walk?
That sounds doable! I could definitely manage that.
Awesome! It might help you reconnect with your creative side and provide a little joy in your day.
Yeah, I think so too.
How about your roommates? Have you had a chance to reconnect with them since your last session?
Not really. I’ve been so busy with work and trying to get back into a routine that I haven’t made an effort.
Would it be helpful to reach out to them? Maybe suggest a fun activity?
Yeah, I think I should. It would be nice to break the ice again.
What kind of activity do you think would work?
Maybe a movie night or a game night? Something low-key.
That sounds perfect! It could help you all reconnect and lighten the mood.
I’ll try to set that up soon.
Excellent! How have you been feeling about your job search?
Honestly, it’s been frustrating. I apply to jobs but don’t hear back, and it just makes me feel like I’m not good enough.
It’s tough out there, and it’s easy to internalize those rejections. Have you thought about what you want from your next job?
Yeah, definitely something more creative and engaging. I want to feel like I’m making a difference, not just sitting at a desk.
That’s a good insight. Maybe we can brainstorm some job options that align with those values?
I’d like that.
Great! What about photography? Have you thought about pursuing it more seriously?
I have, but it feels so daunting. Like, I don’t know where to start.
What if we break it down into smaller steps?
Okay, like what?
Maybe start by creating a portfolio of your best work or reaching out to local photographers for advice?
That could work! I’ll feel more confident if I have something to show.
Exactly! And it could open up new opportunities for you.
Yeah, I like that idea.
How’s your relationship with your boyfriend? Have things improved since we last talked?
A little. We had a good conversation after I got back, but we still have our moments.
Communication is key. Have you both been able to express your feelings openly?
Yeah, we’ve been trying. It’s just hard sometimes when we get caught up in our own frustrations.
That’s completely normal. It might help to schedule regular check-ins, just to talk about how you’re both feeling.
That’s a good idea! I think it would help us stay connected.
I’m glad you think so! Remember, it’s okay to lean on each other during tough times.
I will. Thanks, Ellie.
Of course! So, let’s summarize today’s session. You’ll aim to take a photo every day, reach out to your roommates, and consider taking more steps towards photography. Does that sound good?
Yes, I feel good about that!
Wonderful! I look forward to hearing how it goes in our next session.
Me too! See you next time!
Bye, Tatiana!
